                                                                                                                       7                                      IPL TRIVIA
                            
	The Chennai Super Kings (CSK) are the only side to have reached the semi-finals of all three editions of the IPL.         
	The Kolkata Knight Riders (KKR) are the only side not to have made it to the last four stage ever.         
	Except for the Mumbai Indians, all the other semi-finalists lost their opening game of IPL 2010.         
	The IPL semi-finals in all three editions have featured three Indian captains and one foreign captain. The foreign captain has always been an Australian.         
	Three of last years semi-finalists have qualified this year as well. The Delhi DareDevils have missed out.         
	Subramaniam Badrinath, Suresh Raina (CSK) and Adam Gilchrist (Deccan Chargers) have played every single game of their side so far in three editions of the IPL.         
	Suresh Raina is the only player to have scored 400-plus runs in every edition, while Irfan Pathan is the only bowler to have taken 15 or more wickets.         
	KKRs Manoj Tiwary has the unique distinction of being the only player to be dismissed off the first ball of the tournament.         
